    {
      "id": "r0mr_z9L_IJRZHKnESnBt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -233.29296875,
      "y": 4783.68359375,
      "width": 1007.099365234375,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0r",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1495747558,
      "version": 333,
      "versionNonce": 1204120934,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1784728159771,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\"Why use two Redis data structures instead of only the Sorted Set?\"\n\n\"The Sorted Set is optimized for ranking, but its score is an internal value used only for ordering. \nThe UI needs user-friendly fields like problemsSolved and completionTime, \nso I would store those separately in a Redis Hash. \nThis avoids hitting the database for every leaderboard request while keeping reads entirely in memory.\"",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\"Why use two Redis data structures instead of only the Sorted Set?\"\n\n\"The Sorted Set is optimized for ranking, but its score is an internal value used only for ordering. \nThe UI needs user-friendly fields like problemsSolved and completionTime, \nso I would store those separately in a Redis Hash. \nThis avoids hitting the database for every leaderboard request while keeping reads entirely in memory.\"",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
